The paper discusses the evolution of communication systems towards 4G and beyond, which is a topic related to network infrastructure (cs.NI) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC). The focus of the paper is on cloudifying the 3GPP IMS, which is a service delivery platform, and thus, the paper is also related to software development (cs.SD) and computer engineering (cs.CE). Additionally, the paper discusses the architecture and design of the IMS, which is related to augmented reality (cs.AR) as it involves the integration of virtual and real-world environments.
